\displaystyle\sum_0^n 2^i = 2^{n + 1} - 1
n=m
\implies \sum_0^m 2^i = 2^{m + 1} - 1
\implies \sum_0^{m+1}2^i =\sum_0^m 2^i +2^{m+1}= 2^{m + 1} - 1 +2^{m+1}=2^{m+1}(1+1)-1=2^{m+2}-1
2^{n+2}-2^{n+1}=2^{n+1}
